The paper discusses the design of mechanisms for two-sided markets with incomplete information, adverse selection, and moral hazard, which are central topics in game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of payment, assessment, and matching rules, which are common tools in algorithmic mechanism design (cs.DS) and computational economics (cs.EC).
